                <head>Committed Suicide</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Frederick</ln>
                        <fn>Charles Louis</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Lambert</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Dr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Miller</ln>
                        <fn>Daniel</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Brandt</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Sheriff</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Charles Louis Frederick, aka "Dutch Lewis," committed suicide in his
                    hospital room after being left by his attendant. "His mind has been somewhat
                    impaired, though he was never known to meditate any attempt upon his own life."
                    He had lived for a while with Dr. Lambert and later Daniel Miller, and had been
                    on of the "institutions" of Chambersburg. Sheriff Brandt discovered his body.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
